Section 1 – Definitions.

*   Adapted MaterialApplies to material subject to Copyright and Similar Rights that is derived from or based upon the Licensed Material and requires permission under the Copyright and Similar Rights held by the Licensor. For musical works, performance, or sound recordings, Adapted Material is always produced when the Licensed Material is synchronized with a moving image.
*   Adapter’s License refers to the license You apply to Your Copyright and Similar Rights in Your contributions to Adapted Material according to this Public License.
*   BY-NC-SA Compatible License is a license approved by Creative Commons as essentially equivalent to this Public License, listed at creativecommons.org/compatiblelicenses.
*   Copyright and Similar Rights includes copyright and/or closely related rights like performance, broadcast, sound recording, and Sui Generis Database Rights, regardless of labeling. Rights specified in Section 2(b)(1)-(2) are not considered Copyright and Similar Rights.
*   Effective Technological Measures are those measures that, without proper authority, may not be circumvented under laws fulfilling obligations under Article 11 of the WIPO Copyright Treaty (1996) and/or similar international agreements.
*   Exceptions and Limitations include fair use, fair dealing, and/or any other exception or limitation to Copyright and Similar Rights applicable to Your use of the Licensed Material.
*   License Elements are the attributes listed in the name of a Creative Commons Public License. For this Public License, they are Attribution, NonCommercial, and ShareAlike.
*   Licensed Material is the artistic or literary work, database, or other material to which the Licensor applied this Public License.
*   Licensed Rights are the rights granted to You under this Public License, limited to Copyright and Similar Rights applicable to Your use of the Licensed Material and which the Licensor has authority to license.
*   Licensor is the individual(s) or entity(ies) granting rights under this Public License.
*   NonCommercial means not primarily intended for or directed towards commercial advantage or monetary compensation. Exchange of Licensed Material for other Copyright and Similar Rights material via digital file-sharing or similar means is NonCommercial if no monetary payment is involved.
*   Share means to provide material to the public by any means requiring permission under the Licensed Rights (e.g., reproduction, public display, distribution) and to make material available for public access.
*   Sui Generis Database Rights are rights other than copyright resulting from Directive 96/9/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 11 March 1996 on the legal protection of databases, as amended and/or succeeded, and equivalent rights worldwide.
*   You refers to the individual or entity exercising the Licensed Rights under this Public License. Your has a corresponding meaning.

